==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[lignum|līgnum]] "wood" + [[-fy|-ify]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈlɪgnɪfaɪ/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|lignif|i|ed}}

#{{intransitive}} To become [[wood]].
#{{intransitive}}, {{botany}}: To develop [[woody]] [[tissue]] as a result of [[secondary growth]].
#{{intransitive}}, (''by extension''): To become [[rigid]] or [[fixed]], like something made of wood.

